<p id="Par22">The formulas (
 <xref rid="Equ10" ref-type="">10</xref>), (
 <xref rid="Equ11" ref-type="">11</xref>) for the 3D displacement-field function 
 <inline-formula id="IEq30">
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M81">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$f({\bf{r}}-{{\bf{r}}}_{0})$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M82">
    <mi>f</mi>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>
      <mo>−</mo>
      <msub>
       <mrow>
        <mi mathvariant="bold">r</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mn>0</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mo stretchy="true">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41598_2019_50833_Article_IEq30.gif" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> are the basic theoretical expressions for solving the inverse problem XRDT under consideration. Finally, one has to determine the error-functional (the target function) and generate its optimization procedure. The latter has to apply to the target function in the standard form as follows
 <disp-formula id="Equ12">
  <label>12</label>
  <alternatives>
   <tex-math id="M83">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\begin{array}{rcl}{\rm{\chi }}2 &amp; = &amp; \tfrac{1}{n\{X(T)\,\ast \,Y(T)\}}\,\mathop{\sum }\limits_{i=1}^{n}\,n({{\Phi }}_{i})\,\sum _{\{X(T),Y(T)\}}\,\tfrac{{({I}_{h,obs}[X(T),Y(T);{{\Phi }}_{i}]-{I}_{h,calc}[X(T),Y(T);{{\Phi }}_{i}])}^{2}}{{I}_{h,obs}{[X(T),Y(T);{{\Phi }}_{i}]}^{2}}=Min,\\ n({{\Phi }}_{i}) &amp; = &amp; 1,i=1,\ldots n,\end{array}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M84" display="block">
